On this day, 60 years ago, Michael Jackson was born. The “King of Pop” would go on to change the course of music history across the world. The one-time most popular man on earth made an impression with his moonwalks, robot dance move and his innovative videos. His albums were world bestsellers including Thriller “the best-selling album of all time” which sold over 66 million copies. Read More: Remembering Fela Kuti: Top 12 Songs In honour of his birthday, here is a list of songs for your reflection: Thriller  Man In The Mirror  Smooth Criminal  Beat It  Billy Jean  Black Or White  Speechless  The Way You Make Me Feel  Bad  Dangerous  Blood On The Dancefloor  Do You Remember The Time  Heal The World 